hters direction; it would distract you from sad thoughts. Now go to bed at once, and put yourself to sleep with a good mystery story.”

On the porch he pumped Pnin’s unresponsive hand with enough vigor for two. Then he flourished his cane and merrily marched down the wooden steps.

The screen door banged behind him.

“Der arme Kerl,” muttered kindhearted Hagen to himself as he walked homeward. “At least, I have sweetened the pill.”





